# RAG-Based Document Q&A System Using Endee Vector Database

A complete AI/ML project demonstrating **Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG)** using **Endee** as the vector database. Users upload documents (PDF/TXT), the system indexes them in Endee, and then allows natural language Q&A over the documents.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **LLM API Key**: The Q&A answer generation step requires an LLM. I plan to use the **Groq API** (free tier available at console.groq.com) with `llama3-8b-8192` model. The user needs a free Groq API key. Alternatively, the system falls back to showing retrieved chunks without LLM synthesis if no key is provided.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **GitHub Steps (manual)**: The assignment requires you to:
> 1. **Star** the Endee repo: https://github.com/endee-io/endee
> 2. **Fork** the repo to your personal GitHub account
> 3. Create a **new GitHub repository** for your project and push the code there
> I will create all the code locally; you will need to push it to GitHub.

