---

### Backend (Python/FastAPI)

#### [NEW] `docker-compose.yml`
Spins up the Endee vector database server on port 8080 using the official Docker image.

#### [NEW] `requirements.txt`
```
fastapi
uvicorn
endee
sentence-transformers
PyMuPDF  # for PDF parsing
python-multipart
groq
python-dotenv
requests
```

#### [NEW] `backend/endee_client.py`
- Connects to Endee at `http://localhost:8080`
- Creates an index named `documents` with dimension=384 (matching all-MiniLM-L6-v2), cosine similarity
- Provides `upsert_chunks()` and `search()` helper functions

#### [NEW] `backend/embedder.py`
- Loads `sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2` (dimension=384, free & fast)
- Provides `embed(texts: list[str]) -> list[list[float]]`

#### [NEW] `backend/document_processor.py`
- Reads PDF (via PyMuPDF) or TXT files
- Splits text into overlapping chunks (512 chars, 50 char overlap)
- Returns list of `{"id", "text", "source", "chunk_index"}` dicts

#### [NEW] `backend/llm_client.py`
- Uses Groq Python SDK to call `llama3-8b-8192`
- Takes `query + context_chunks` → returns synthesized answer
- Falls back gracefully if no API key

#### [NEW] `backend/app.py`
FastAPI app with these endpoints:
| Endpoint | Method | Description |
|----------|--------|-------------|
| `GET /health` | GET | Health check |
| `POST /upload` | POST | Upload + ingest document into Endee |
| `POST /search` | POST | Semantic search, returns top-k chunks |
| `POST /ask` | POST | Full RAG: search + LLM answer generation |
| `GET /documents` | GET | List all ingested documents |
| `DELETE /documents/{doc_id}` | DELETE | Remove a document's chunks |

---

### Frontend (HTML/CSS/JS)

#### [NEW] `frontend/index.html` + `frontend/style.css` + `frontend/app.js`
Modern dark-themed single-page app with:
- **Upload Panel**: Drag-and-drop or click to upload PDF/TXT
- **Chat Interface**: Natural language Q&A with streamed responses
- **Semantic Search**: Pure vector search mode showing matching chunks with similarity scores
- **Document Manager**: List of indexed documents with delete option

---

### Documentation

#### [NEW] `README.md`
Comprehensive README covering:
- Project overview and what it demonstrates
- System architecture diagram (ASCII/text)
